{"comments":"Brush Engine Types — Rendering algorithms for different brush behaviors.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nDifferent brush effects require fundamentally different rendering\napproaches. A pixel stamping engine is fast but limited. A bristle\nsimulation provides natural media feel but costs more computation.\nThe engine choice determines the brush's capability envelope.\n\n## Engine Categories\n\n- **Raster**: PixelEngine, SmudgeEngine, CloneEngine\n- **Simulation**: BristleEngine, ParticleEngine\n- **Vector**: VectorEngine\n- **Effect**: SymmetryEngine, PatternEngine\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[72,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Engine/Types.purs","start":[72,3]},"title":"PixelEngine"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[74,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Engine/Types.purs","start":[74,3]},"title":"BristleEngine"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[76,19],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Engine/Types.purs","start":[76,3]},"title":"ParticleEngine"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[78,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Engine/Types.purs","start":[78,3]},"title":"VectorEngine"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[80,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Engine/Types.purs","start":[80,3]},"title":"SmudgeEngine"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[82,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Engine/Types.purs","start":[82,3]},"title":"CloneEngine"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[84,19],"name":"../../hydroge